{"fixed_xml":"<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<ITEM>
  In denen Thurneysischen Buchl\u221a\u00a7den allhier, seynd dato folgende zwey B\u221a\u00bacher zu haben, so in Nancy durch S\u221a\u00babscriptiones gedruckt worden.
  <BIBL>
    <TITLE>Dictionnaire Universel- Francois & Latin, Vulgairement appell\u221a\u00a9 Dictionaire de Trevoux</TITLE>, avec des Remarques d Erudition & de Critique
    <VOLUME>5. Tom.</VOLUME>
    <FORMAT>fol.</FORMAT>
    <YEAR>1741</YEAR>;
    davon die 3. ersten Tom. dato schon zu beziehen sind; das gantze Werck kostet samt der Fracht
    <PRICE>fl. 24</PRICE>
  </BIBL>
  <BIBL>
    <TITLE>Dictionaire Oeconomique, continant les moyens d'Augmenter son dien & de conserver sa sante</TITLE>, par <AUTHOR>Mister Noel Chomel</AUTHOR>, Augmente dun Nouveau Supplement de deur Volumes, par <AUTHOR>F. Marset, Doct. en Medecines</AUTHOR>.
    <FORMAT>2vec fig.</FORMAT>
    <VOLUME>4. Tom.</VOLUME>
    <FORMAT>fol.</FORMAT>
    <YEAR>1741</YEAR>;
    davon der erste Tomus dato bey ihnen zu beziehen ist; di\u221a\u00fc gantze Werck kostet samt der Fracht
    <PRICE>fl. 18</PRICE>
  </BIBL>
  So dann sind bey ihnen auch genugsam annoch zu haben:
  <BIBL>
    <TITLE>Dictionaire Historique & Critique de Mr. Bayle</TITLE>-
    <VOLUME>4. Tom.</VOLUME>
    <FORMAT>fol.</FORMAT>
    <PLACE>Amsterd.</PLACE>
    <YEAR>1740</YEAR>.
    \u221a\u2020
    <PRICE>L. 27</PRICE>
  </BIBL>
  <BIBL>
    <TITLE>Corpus Juris Civilis Romani, cum Notis Gotofrest</TITLE>
    <VOLUME>2. Tom.</VOLUME>
    <FORMAT>fol.</FORMAT>
    <YEAR>1740</YEAR>.
    \u221a\u2020
    <PRICE>fl. 10. 48. xr.</PRICE>
  </BIBL>
  <BIBL>
    <TITLE>Dictionaire Royal, Francois-Allemand-Latin, par le R. P. Fr. Pomey</TITLE>
    <VOLUME>3. Voll.</VOLUME>
    <FORMAT>4\u221a\u2264.</FORMAT>
    <YEAR>1741</YEAR>.
    \u221a\u2020
    <PRICE>fl. 5. 24. xr.</PRICE>
  </BIBL>
</ITEM>
","number_of_corrections":5,"explanation":"Fixed malformed/mismatched tags and added an XML declaration. Changes made:
- Added XML declaration <?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?> at the top.
- Normalized monetary element names: replaced inconsistent <PRIZE> / </PRIZE> usages with <PRICE> / </PRICE> (4 occurrences adjusted, including one mismatched opening/closing pair).
- Escaped ampersands as & where they appear in text (e.g. "Francois & Latin").
- Ensured all <BIBL> blocks are properly closed and that the overall <ITEM> root is balanced.
I did not alter the original visible textual glyphs beyond escaping/normalizing XML entities; sequences like \u221a and \u2020 were preserved as in the source (escaped in the JSON string) because their intended typographic values are uncertain."}
